---
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';

const rtcf = [
  {
    letter: 'R',
    word: 'Role',
    body: 'Assign the AI a persona. "You are a senior copywriter." "You are a CFO advising a startup." This anchors the model in a perspective.',
  },
  {
    letter: 'T',
    word: 'Task',
    body: 'State exactly what you want it to do. "Draft a one-page memo." "Summarize this in five bullets." Be specific.',
  },
  {
    letter: 'C',
    word: 'Context',
    body: 'Fill in the relevant background. Who is the audience? What constraints exist? What have you already tried? More context = better output.',
  },
  {
    letter: 'F',
    word: 'Format',
    body: 'Tell it the shape you want back. Bullet list? Markdown table? Email? 200 words or 2000? Examples beat abstract instructions.',
  },
];

const workflow = [
  {
    step: '01',
    title: 'Use AI?',
    body: 'Decide if this is a good use case. Routine, pattern-following, low-stakes? Yes. Novel, high-stakes, or requires private judgement? Maybe not.',
  },
  {
    step: '02',
    title: 'Set Up the Prompt',
    body: 'Use the RTCF framework. Lay the foundation in your first message — Role, Task, Context, Format.',
  },
  {
    step: '03',
    title: 'Have a Conversation',
    body: 'Don\'t accept the first draft. Refine. Redirect. Ask for alternatives. Say what you don\'t like.',
  },
  {
    step: '04',
    title: 'Verify and Finish',
    body: 'You are the final reviewer. Fact-check anything that matters. Tighten the voice. Make it yours before it ships.',
  },
];
---
<Section id="how-to-use" number="03" title="How to Use AI" band="light">
  <p>
    The single biggest factor in getting a great answer from AI is the quality of what you send it.
    A simple framework — and the willingness to keep talking to it — does most of the work.
  </p>

  <h3>The RTCF Prompting Framework</h3>
  <div class="rtcf-grid">
    {rtcf.map((r) => (
      <div class="rtcf-card">
        <div class="rtcf-letter">{r.letter}</div>
        <div class="rtcf-word">{r.word}</div>
        <p>{r.body}</p>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>

  <h3>Before vs. After: A Simple Example</h3>
  <div class="two-col" style="grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;">
    <div>
      <p style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--med-gray);">Lazy prompt</p>
      <div class="prompt-block">Give me a good chicken recipe for dinner.</div>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p style="font-weight: 600; color: var(--brand-blue);">RTCF prompt</p>
      <div class="prompt-block">You are a weeknight home-cook coach. Give me a chicken recipe I can make for two people in under 35 minutes using ingredients I likely have in a basic pantry. Skip anything that needs to marinate. Format as: title, ingredients (with substitutions), 5–7 numbered steps, and a "what to serve with it" line.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3>It's a Conversation</h3>
  <p>
    Don't accept the first response. Refine. Redirect. Repeat. That's how you get great work — same as
    working with a junior teammate who's brilliant but needs guidance. "Make it shorter." "More skeptical."
    "Try it from the other person's point of view." Each exchange compounds.
  </p>

  <h3>You Still Matter</h3>
  <p>
    AI is a force multiplier, not a replacement. You bring the taste, the judgement, the relationships,
    the accountability. Humans are still an essential element of every AI workflow — and the people who
    do best with these tools are the ones who stay in the loop, not the ones who try to outsource themselves.
  </p>

  <h3>A Sample Workflow</h3>
  <p>
    Five steps that turn a one-shot prompt into a real working session. The middle three are where the
    actual quality lives — most people skip straight from <em>Use AI?</em> to <em>Polish</em>, and that's
    why their results disappoint.
  </p>
  <figure class="slide-figure">
    <img
      src="/images/sample-workflow.png"
      alt="Sample workflow: 01 Use AI? — Determine if it's a good use case. 02 Framework — Create a conversation foundation. 03 Refine — Use follow-up requests to refine. 04 Review — You are the taste maker. 05 Polish — Small manual changes if needed."
      loading="lazy"
      width="1600"
      height="900"
    />
  </figure>
</Section>

<style>
  .rtcf-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: 20px;
    margin: 30px 0;
  }
  .rtcf-card {
    padding: 28px;
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 102, 204, 0.25);
    border-left: 5px solid var(--brand-blue);
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0, 31, 63, 0.05);
  }
  .rtcf-letter {
    font-size: 56px;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--brand-blue);
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
  }
  .rtcf-word {
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--dark-gray);
    margin: 4px 0 12px 0;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }
  .rtcf-card p {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--dark-gray);
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
